description:
The Sweet DVD complete collection

This was my first DVD I created several years ago (2003) when I learned how to make DVDs. 
Maybe a directors cut could be needed but I hope you like the content :-). 

This DVD contains:
- all popular music videos from the glam rock band The Sweet from the 1970&amp;#039;s
- live performances, rare documentaries and interviews 
- bonus material with newer songmixes, great for the party, listen to the rave version of Hell Raiser!
- several hours of videos! A unique DVD for all Sweet fans.
This DVD does not contain:
- material from the post-Sweet period, except from an interview from 1990.

Most of the videos are VCD quality but ok to watch and listen to.

The DVD content:
Video menu
- Ballroom Blitz
- BBC Documentary (the only two official documentaries from 1974 and 1976)
- Poppa joe
- Co-Co
- Little Willy
- Wig wam bam
- Blockbuster
- Turn it down
- Teenage rampage
- Fox on the run
- Action
- Hell raiser
- Desolation boulevard clips (music videos, including Andy Scott solos, and private videos, rare!)
- Private collection 2 (music videos, tv adverts, private videos and Andy Scott video )
- Tower records interview 1990
- Love is like oxygen
Audio menu
- Greatest hits remixed, the glam goth techno mixes 
( Rosetta Stone, Die Krupps, Nitzer Ebb, Alien Sex Fiend, Sheep on Drugs, Mission UK and more)
- It&amp;#039;s the Sweet mix, 1985 Anagram 12&quot;

